{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"IntersectionObserverEntry.isIntersecting","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/isIntersecting","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Intersection_Observer_API\">Intersection Observer API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry\"><code>IntersectionObserverEntry</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/boundingClientRect\"><code>boundingClientRect</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/intersectionRatio\"><code>intersectionRatio</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/intersectionRect\"><code>intersectionRect</code></a></li><li><em><code>isIntersecting</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/rootBounds\"><code>rootBounds</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/target\"><code>target</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/time\"><code>time</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Intersection Observer API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserver\"><code>IntersectionObserver</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/indexedDB\"><code>indexedDB</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry\"><code>IntersectionObserverEntry</code></a> interface's\n  read-only <strong><code>isIntersecting</code></strong> property is a Boolean value\n  which is <code>true</code> if the target element intersects with the intersection\n  observer's root. If this is <code>true</code>, then, the\n  <code>IntersectionObserverEntry</code> describes a transition into a state of\n  intersection; if it's <code>false</code>, then you know the transition is from\n  intersecting to not-intersecting.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  A Boolean value which indicates whether the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/target\" title=\"target\"><code>target</code></a> element has transitioned into\n  a state of intersection (<code>true</code>) or out of a state of intersection\n  (<code>false</code>).\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  In this simple example, an intersection callback is used to update a counter of how\n  many targeted elements are currently intersecting with the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserver/root\" title=\"intersection root\">intersection root</a>.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">intersectionCallback</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">entries</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  entries<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">forEach</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">entry</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>entry<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>isIntersecting<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      intersectingCount <span class=\"token operator\">+=</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      intersectingCount <span class=\"token operator\">-=</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>\n  To see a more concrete example, take a look at\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Intersection_Observer_API/Timing_element_visibility#handling_intersection_changes\">Handling intersection changes</a> in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Intersection_Observer_API/Timing_element_visibility\">Timing element visibility with the Intersection Observer API</a>.\n</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/IntersectionObserver/#dom-intersectionobserverentry-isintersecting","title":"Intersection Observer"}],"query":"api.IntersectionObserverEntry.isIntersecting"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.IntersectionObserverEntry.isIntersecting","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/isIntersecting/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The IntersectionObserverEntry interface's\n  read-only isIntersecting property is a Boolean value\n  which is true if the target element intersects with the intersection\n  observer's root. If this is true, then, the\n  IntersectionObserverEntry describes a transition into a state of\n  intersection; if it's false, then you know the transition is from\n  intersecting to not-intersecting.","popularity":0.0012,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:14:42.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/intersectionobserverentry/isintersecting","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/intersectionobserverentry/isintersecting/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/277e5969c63b97cfb55ab4a0e612e8040810f49b","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry","title":"IntersectionObserverEntry"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserverEntry/isIntersecting","title":"IntersectionObserverEntry.isIntersecting"}],"pageTitle":"IntersectionObserverEntry.isIntersecting - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}